        "rootCause": "Node dev-worker-0.redhat-internal.com is experiencing rapid disk exhaustion on /var/lib/kubelet (5GiB ext4 loopback device) driven by four demo-diskpressure workloads deliberately writing unbounded data to emptyDir volumes, consuming ~100MB/min and projected to exhaust remaining ~1.57GiB free space within ~15 minutes. The primary structural offender is postgres-emptydir, which uses a 4Gi emptyDir for PostgreSQL PGDATA — a stateful database running on ephemeral node-local storage. All pods tolerate the disk-pressure taint, preventing Kubernetes self-eviction.",
        "rootCauseAnalysis": {
            "contributingFactors": [
                "log-collector pod writes 256KB random files every 5 seconds (unbounded loop) to emptyDir — continuous growing writer",
                "nginx-cache init container wrote ~200MB of random data in one burst at pod startup",
                "redis-scratch session-loader sidecar wrote ~100MB random AOF segments to shared emptyDir",
                "postgres-emptydir uses a 4Gi emptyDir for PostgreSQL PGDATA — active WAL and data file writes on node-local disk (primary structural cause)",
                "All pods tolerate node.kubernetes.io/disk-pressure taint — prevents Kubernetes auto-eviction self-healing",
                "All pods co-located on dev-worker-0 via nodeSelector, concentrating disk load on a single 5GiB loopback device",
                "Kubelet had 3 restarts in prior ~48 minutes (02:32, 02:55, 03:19) indicating recurring prior disk pressure events",
                "Disk fill rate ~100MB/min with ~1.57GiB remaining — exhaustion projected in ~15 minutes"
            ],
            "remediationTarget": {
                "kind": "Deployment",
                "name": "postgres-emptydir",
                "namespace": "demo-diskpressure"
            },
            "severity": "high",
            "signalType": "DiskPressure",
            "summary": "Node dev-worker-0.redhat-internal.com is experiencing rapid disk exhaustion on /var/lib/kubelet (5GiB ext4 loopback device) driven by four demo-diskpressure workloads deliberately writing unbounded data to emptyDir volumes, consuming ~100MB/min and projected to exhaust remaining ~1.57GiB free space within ~15 minutes. The primary structural offender is postgres-emptydir, which uses a 4Gi emptyDir for PostgreSQL PGDATA — a stateful database running on ephemeral node-local storage. All pods tolerate the disk-pressure taint, preventing Kubernetes self-eviction."
        },
